This paper deals with the determination of weight distributions and complete weight enumerators of linear codes, which are important topics in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The applications of linear codes with a few weights in authentication codes, secret sharing, and consumer electronics suggest that this paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of distributed systems (cs.DS) and computer communications (cs.CC). Additionally, the use of Legendre symbol in deriving the Hamming weight distributions may indicate a connection to signal processing and information retrieval (cs.SI).
